title: L'Illusionniste
description:
The Illusionist (French: L'Illusionniste) is a 2010 

French-Scottish animated comedy-drama film directed by Sylvain Chomet. 

The film is based on an unproduced script written by French mime, director and actor 

            Jacques Tati in 1956. 


Controversy surrounds Tati's motivation for the script, which was written as a personal letter to his estranged eldest daughter, Helga Marie-Jeanne in collaboration with his long-term writing partner Henri Marquet, between writing for the films Mon Oncle and Play Time

A piece of Art , real animation movie as we like ; real cinema
